But where, how, and what? I have blustered for pre
rogative; I have bellowed for freedom; I have offered to serve my country; I have engaged to betray it;
a master-stroke, truly; why, I have talk'd treason, writ treason, and if a man can't live by that he can live by nothing Here I set up as a bookseller; why men left off reading; and if I was to turn butcher, I believe o' my conscience they'd leave off eating.

